{{Infobox person | image = <!-- Only freely-licensed images may be used to depict living people. See [[WP:NONFREE]]. --> | image_size = 150px | | birth_name = Georges Nicolas Hayek Jr. | name = Nick Hayek Jr. | birth_date = {{birth date and age |1954|10|23|df=y}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = Businessman | title = CEO [[Swatch Group]] | parents = [[Nicolas Hayek|Nicolas George Hayek]] (father) | relatives = [[Nayla Hayek]] (sister) }}
'''Georges Nicolas "Nick" Hayek Jr.''' (born 23 October 1954) is a Swiss-Lebanese businessman.
== Early life and education == Hayek is the son of Lebanese-born [[Nicolas Hayek|Nicolas George Hayek]], the late co-founder of the [[The Swatch Group Ltd.|Swatch Group]].
He attended the [[University of St. Gallen]], and CLSF, a cinema school in Paris. He also attended [[Institut Montana Zugerberg|Institut Montana]] in [[Zug|Zug, Switzerland]] <ref>http://www.swatchgroup.com/en/group_profile/boards/executive_group_management_board/nick_hayek</ref>
== Career == In 2003, Hayek Jr. became the CEO of the [[Swatch Group]].<ref>Swatch Group Management Board: http://www.swatchgroup.com/company/organs.php</ref>
The Hayek family controls approximately 39% of The Swatch Group.
== Personal life == He has a sister [[Nayla Hayek|Nayla]] and two children.
